Southern National Corp. said it agreed to merge with an Elkin, N.C., thrift in a stock swap valued at $23.7 million. 

Southern National said it offered 1.6 million shares of stock for all the stock and stock options outstanding of Mutual Federal Savings & Loan Association.
The agreement is subject to approval by federal and state regulators and shareholders of Mutual Federal. 

Southern National is the parent company of the sixth-largest bank in North Carolina, with 139 branches. 

